for or on behalf of a commercial entity.

"Commercial Use" means any use of the Software that is intended for, directed
toward, or used in connection with commercial advantage, monetary compensation,
or revenue-generating activity. Commercial Use includes, without limitation:

  a. selling, licensing, renting, hosting, or providing the Software or its
     functionality as a product, service, or paid feature;
  b. including the Software in, or using it to develop, test, operate, monitor,
     support, or promote, a commercial product or service;
  c. internal business use by or for a for-profit entity;
  d. paid consulting, integration, training, support, or managed services; and
  e. use for which a person or entity receives compensation or commercial
     benefit, whether direct or indirect.

Nonprofit status, free distribution, or charging only distribution costs does
not by itself make a use noncommercial. If there is doubt, the use is not
licensed unless the Licensor confirms in writing that it is noncommercial.

"Written Approval" means a specific written permission signed by the Licensor,
or an electronic permission sent from an account publicly identified with the
Licensor, that identifies the recipient and the permitted Commercial Use.
General statements, public repository access, issue or pull-request discussion,
and acceptance of a contribution are not Written Approval.

